    <chapter>
      <heading>
        Software documentation for the MPGOFeatureFlags class
      </heading>
      <class name="MPGOFeatureFlags" super="NSObject">
        <declared>MPGOFeatureFlags.h</declared>
        <desc>
          Versioning and feature-flag utility for MPGO file
          format v0.2+. Every file written by v0.2+ carries two
          root-group attributes: @mpeg_o_format_version =
          "1.1" (major.minor string) @mpeg_o_features = JSON
          array of feature strings v0.1 files have
          @mpeg_o_version = "1.0.0" instead and no
          @mpeg_o_features — readers detect the old
          format by the absence of the feature-flags attribute
          and fall back to the v0.1 JSON paths. Features without an
          `opt_` prefix are required: a reader must refuse a
          file that names a required feature it does not support.
          Features with `opt_` are informational — readers may
          skip them.
        </desc>
        <method type="NSString*" factory="yes">
          <sel>featureAnonymized</sel>
          <desc>
            <em>Description forthcoming.</em>
          </desc>
        </method>
